4.11 Computing FPCA in R
The core function in the fda package is

pca_object <- pca.fd(
  fdobj,
  nharm=3,
  centerfns=TRUE
)

The most important output elements are:

pca_object$harmonics  # estimated eigenfunctions
pca_object$values     # estimated eigenvalues
pca_object$varprop    # proportions of variance explained
pca_object$scores     # one score per curve and component
pca_object$meanfd     # estimated mean function

A useful workflow is:

inspect and clean the raw data;
smooth the individual curves using an appropriate basis and penalty;
inspect the mean and covariance;
run FPCA;
choose the number of components using explained variance and interpretability;
plot \(\widehat\mu\pm c\sqrt{\widehat\lambda_k}\widehat v_k\);
inspect score plots and relate scores to observed characteristics;
use the scores in subsequent statistical models if appropriate.
